    <h3>
        Popular use-cases for OCR technology
    </h3>
    <p data-aos="fade-right">

        Probably the most well known use case for OCR is converting printed paper documents into machine-readable text
        documents. Once a scanned paper document went through OCR processing, the text of the document can be edited
        with word processors like Microsoft Word or Google Docs. Before OCR technology was available, the only option to
        digitise printed paper documents was to manually re-typing the text. Not only was thi massively time consuming,
        it also came with inaccuracy and typing errors.

        OCR is often used as a “hidden” technology, powering many well known systems and services in our daily life.
        Less known, but as important, use cases for OCR technology include data entry automation, indexing documents for
