        But programmers can not detect every language, especially not less popular and older ones. They also often like
        to search and group source code by programming language. Some websites and infrastructure like GitHub will try
        to classify source code based on some heuristics, like the file extension or the presence of some string, for
        example using regular expressions. When the file contains for example the string SELECT * and the file extension
        is .sql, this may be evidence that the query language SQL is used.</p>
